bio.experienceSummary:
I am currently a toddler teacher. I have 14 children in my class between the ages of 2 and 3.
Over the summer I was an infant caregiver. I had 2-month-old babies up to 18 months.
I am CPR and first aid certified.
I have a clean background history.
I have been babysitting for family friends for certain occasions for 2 years.
I was also a lead assistant at a Montessori for 2 1/2 years, dealing with children ages 18 months - 6 years.
Highly educated care taker who can assist kids on homework, certified CPR/AED/First aid. Will help in cooking especially vegetarian food. I will commute your kids.

As a caregiver with over a decade of experience, my passion for caring for children stems from my positive babysitting experiences and my genuine desire to make a difference in their lives. I believe in supporting families and providing a dependable childcare option that allows parents peace of mind.

My patient, calm, and friendly nature allows me to connect with children effortlessly. I foster creativity and imagination through engaging activities, making each day an enriching experience.

Open and effective communication is key to my approach. Whether it's verbal updates during pickup, regular text messages, or phone calls, I ensure parents are informed about their child's day and any matters that arise.

I am exceptionally comfortable enforcing household rules, ensuring a safe and consistent environment for the children in my care.

From outdoor sports to board games and puzzles, I enjoy a wide range of games that cater to different interests and age groups.

She is always on time and willing to work if any is needed. My both children love her passion for being who she was. I’m happy with her service that she gave us. By far, miss S was so one of the best sitters that I had. Thank you to Care.com and thank you for your service miss S. See you around.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi, 

My name is LZ and I am scientist here in NJ. I hold a masters degree in statistics and a bachelors in psychology! I have been babysitting for the past 12 years. I speak 3 languages fluently: English, French, and Arabic. I have watched as young as newborns all the way to pre-teens. I have my own car! Please message if interested. 

I'd describe my personality as kind, patient, compassionate.

I started working with kids when 12 years ago! 

In my spare time, I like to babysit, play volleyball with my friends, take long walks in nature, and nap!

Good evening my name is Ashley and I currently work full-time as a childcare provider/nanny.
With over 10 years of experience providing childcare to small children, (and support to their families), I skillfully manage details and give care to the most precious among us in this life. More, I am equipped and experienced at handling stressful situations and can adapt easily to changing needs very quickly. 
I am currently seeking an opportunity where I can apply my extensive child care experience in a role where I can utilize my skills of managing details, caring for others, and seeing projects through to completion. I am polished and professional, and present myself as a mature and responsible go-getter. I have been acknowledged for my talent of getting tasks done and getting them done correctly and on time. 
I am available at your convenience for an interview, and look forward to an opportunity to discuss my credentials in greater detail. 

Sincerely,
Ashley

description.originalText: Ashely is an amazing nanny/baby sitter. She worked for us for almost 3 years during pandemic . My kids adored her . She was very flexible and accommodating. I would strongly recommend Ashley.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello Dear family!
My name is Zamira and I am an experienced nanny and babysitter. I live in Carteret and would love to connect with your family to see if we can be a good match.

- I have 4 years of experience with children from ages of 1-15 years old (Me being +18) and many years of experience helping to take care of my little brother and cousins.
- I speak English (Advanced) and Spanish (Native Speaker). 
- Pet friendly
- Good swimmer
- Non smoker
- Fully vaccinated
- CPR certified
- Love cooking and baking
- Arts and crafts enthusiast
- I enjoy expending time with children and being a caregiver for them. I consider myself friendly, loving, patient, reliable, creative, clean, organized and open minded.
- I'll be happy to share with you my references from the families I've worked for.

Hi! I'm a mother myself of two older girls, ages 26 and 24 both of which were preemies. I am extremely reliable, caring, and nurturing and will be sure to treat your children as if they were my own. I have just recently finished with a wonderful family that I have been with for about 3 years but the family is relocating out of state. Prior to having my own children, I worked in a pediatric office for five years. Feel free to leave a message for me with any questions you should have. Thank you.

description.displayText: Our family loves Lori!  We've been so lucky to have her with us for 2.5 years.  She is everything you'd want as a parent in a nanny - responsible, communicative, punctual, loving and caring.  She sees our kids as hers and treats them the same - reinforcing our schedules and house rules - a true extension of us when we're not there. We couldn't be happier to have found her.

bio.experienceSummary:
I am the mother of four grown children. I am interested in providing my services an expertise to assist parents in babysitting their own children. My genuine love and maternal instincts are truly an asset that any parent would appreciate from a caregiver to their loved one. 

I believe in positive reinforcing, challenge your child through conversation and games and yet being calm, patient and understanding.

I have also worked in the medical field for over 20 years, so my experience with handling all situations is another attribute that would help make parents extremely comfortable with me!

I am interested in 4 full days or 2 full days 8-10 hrs each. Sept 2025 looking forward to a new venture

description.displayText: There are many things I could say about Donna, but most importantly, we trust her with our three young children.  It was not easy for me to find someone I could say that about.  Donna is an experienced mother and has young grandchildren, so she knows what she is doing!  She is comfortable caring for children when they are sick, and is capable of making day to day decisions that are in their best interest.  My children love Donna, and are very comfortable with her and therefore so are we!  Donna is also VERY punctual.  Happy to discuss further by email or phone.
